para_trans: Sant Sewalal Maharaj Banjara / Laman Tanda
The Zilla Parishad, Dhule is headed by
Appointment of Non-Governmental Members to the Committee - 2
Government Decision No: Tansuyo-2024 / Q. No.29 (4) / Aastha-5
Government Decision No: Department of Rural Development, No. Tanda Reforms-2019 / Q. No.67 / Aastha-5, dated 23rd February, 2024.

Preamble: - Department of Rural Development, Government of India Decision No. Tanda Reforms-2019 / Q.67 / Aastha-5, D. Under the Sant Sewalal Maharaj Banjara / Laman Tanda Samriddhi Yojana, a committee has been constituted under the chairmanship of CEO, Zila Parishad to select the work keeping in view the priority and urgency received from the Gram Panchayat and 2 representatives of Banjara / Laman Samaj in the said committee.

There is a provision for appointment as a non-official member. However, since most Zila Parishads had administrators, it was seen necessary to appoint these non-official members from the government level. Considering this, the government was considering appointing non-governmental members to the committee headed by the CEO, Zilla Parishad, Dhule for a period of 3 years from the government level.

Government Decision: - Keeping in view the priority and urgency of the work received from the Gram Panchayat under the Sant Sewalal Maharaj Banjara / Laman Tanda Samriddhi Yojana, 2 representatives of the Banjara / Laman community are being appointed as non-official members in the District Level Committee headed by the CEO, Zila Parishad, Dhule for 3 years as follows.

Since the daily allowance and travel allowance payable to the said non-governmental members on the day of the meeting shall be paid from the 2 per cent of the fund admissible for the administrative expenses of the said scheme, the concerned non-governmental members shall submit the same to the CEO, Zila Parishad, Dhule and the CEO, Zila Parishad, Dhule shall pay the daily allowance to the concerned non-governmental members as per Government rules.
